Construction of onshore facilities has been awarded to a consortium led by Japan’s JGC, UK firm TechnipFMC and US company Fluor Corp, Exxon head of power and gas marketing Peter Clarke told a ceremony in the capital Maputo. The $30 billion Rovuma LNG project has a capacity of 15 million tons a year (mtpa) and is set pump much-needed cash into the southern African nation’s ailing economy. --Reuters--